<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,705,1269]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1173,1197]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
A drawing of the maxilla is available in 
<bibRefCitation author="Parker" box="[769,926,1173,1197]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Parker, H. W. (1949) The snakes of Somaliland and the Sokotra Islands. E. J. Brill, Leiden, 115 pp." type="book" year="1949">
Parker (
<number box="[857,917,1173,1197]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1949.0">1949</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, while a representation the hemipenis is present in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosler" box="[220,495,1209,1233]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Rosler, H. &amp; Wranik, W. (2004) A key and annotated checklist to the reptiles of the Socotra Archipelago. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 20, 505 - 534." type="journal article" year="2004">
Rösler &amp; Wranik (
<number box="[425,487,1209,1233]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The molecular investigations by 
<bibRefCitation box="[871,1075,1209,1234]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Nagy, Z. T., Joger, H., Wink, M., Glaw, F. &amp; Vences, M. (2003) Multiple colonization of Madagascar and Socotra by colubrid snakes: evidence from nuclear and mitochondrial gene phylogenies. Proceedings of the Royal Society, London, ser. B, 270, 2613 - 2621." type="journal article">
Nagy 
<emphasis box="[938,993,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1008,1067,1209,1233]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
allocated 
<taxonomicName box="[1189,1312,1209,1233]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Ditypophis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1312,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ditypophis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[231,463,1245,1269]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudoxyrhophiinae">Pseudoxyrhophiinae</taxonomicName>
, later included by 
<bibRefCitation box="[669,879,1245,1269]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Zaher, H., Gobbi Grazziotin F., Cadle J. E., Murphy R. W., de Moura-Leite J. C. &amp; Bonatto S. L., (2009) Molecular phylogeny of advanced snakes (Serpentes, Caenophidia) with an emphasis on South American Xenodontines: a revised classification and descriptions of new taxa. - Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 49 (11), 115 - 153." type="journal article">
Zaher 
<emphasis box="[741,797,1245,1269]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[812,871,1245,1269]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in the family 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1210,1245,1269]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Lamprophiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
